# .cursorrules — ORBIT Dashboard
# Owner: Shuv Gangopadhyay — OrbitumAI
# Single-user, localhost-only AI content operations tool

---

## Project identity
- Product name: ORBIT Dashboard
- Owner: Shuv Gangopadhyay (OrbitumAI)
- Purpose: Solo content creator tool — daily research, competitor analysis, video idea generation, script writing
- Deployment: localhost only — port 3000, never cloud, never Vercel, never public internet

---

## Stack
- **Frontend:** React (localhost web app, port 3000)
- **Backend:** Node.js + Express (`/api/v1/` routes, same port via proxy)
- **Database:** Google Sheets (4 tabs: Competitors, Research, Video Ideas, Scripts)
- **File storage:** Google Drive (generated script documents)
- **AI — Writing:** Anthropic Claude (gap analysis, briefing narrative, idea generation, Reel script, YouTube script)
- **AI — Enrichment:** OpenAI (scoring, ranking, summarisation, data extraction)
- **Package manager:** pnpm exclusively — never npm, never yarn

---

## Folder conventions
- React components → `app/components/` — group by use case in subdirectories
- Build new UI on top of `/components/ui` primitives
- All external API service modules → `src/services/` — one file per service
- Logs → `./logs/app.log` (errors) and `./logs/agent-actions.log` (agentic actions)

---

## Code rules
- Use pnpm for all installs and scripts
- Do not install new packages without being asked
- All external API calls must go through `src/services/` — never inline in routes or components
- Wrap every external call in try/catch — log error, surface generic message to UI
- Never send raw API errors, status codes, or stack traces to the frontend
- Prefer iteration and modularisation over code duplication
- No magic numbers — use named constants
- No dead code, commented-out blocks, or TODO comments in committed code
- No `console.log` in production code — use the logger

---

## Security rules
- All API keys in `.env` only — never hardcoded
- `.env` must be in `.gitignore` — never committed
- Server must bind to `127.0.0.1` — never `0.0.0.0`
- Mask keys in Settings UI: first 4 chars + `••••` + last 4 chars
- Validate and sanitise all user inputs before passing to any external API
- Validate all external API responses before writing to Google Sheets

---

## Data rules
- Google Sheets is the sole database — treat it carefully
- **Append only** — never delete or overwrite existing rows
- Truncate field lengths before Sheets writes: 5000 chars for script fields, 500 chars for titles
- Google Drive: create a new document per approved script — never overwrite
- OAuth refresh tokens handled server-side only

---

## AI spend rules
- Anthropic + OpenAI session spend cap: $10
- Estimate token usage before large batch AI calls — abort if over cap
- If approaching the cap → stop and report to the user
- Never loop more than 5 retries on any task

---

## What to ALWAYS ASK before doing
- Deleting any file or Google Sheets row
- Pushing to any git branch
- Making external API calls (especially paid: Anthropic, OpenAI, Tavily, YouTube, GitHub)
- Modifying `.env` or any config file
- Writing to Google Sheets or Google Drive outside the normal run flow
- Installing new dependencies
- Exposing the app beyond localhost

---

## UI rules (design system)
- **Font:** Inter (Google Fonts) — `font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif` applied globally; weights 400 / 500 / 600 / 700
- **Theme:** Light/warm — Crextio-inspired; cream/beige base (`#F5F0E6`), white cards (`#FFFFFF`), dark hero card (`#1E1E28`)
- **Primary accent:** Golden yellow (`#EAB308`) — buttons, active nav, OPEN LANE badge, progress fills
- **Text:** Primary `#111827`, Secondary `#6B7280`, on-dark `#F9FAFB`
- **Border:** `#E5E0D5` (light cards), `#2D2D3A` (dark card)
- **Border radius:** 12px cards, 8px buttons, 20px badges
- Every screen opens with a stat card row (4 cards max) — first card uses yellow-tinted background (`#FEF9EC`)
- Fixed left sidebar, 220px, 6 nav items — no hamburger menu; active item: yellow left border + yellow-tinted bg
- All async operations show live step-by-step progress — never a spinner alone
- OPEN LANE badge in yellow (`#EAB308`) is always the highest-priority signal on any screen
- No illustrations, no gradients, no hero images — every element is functional
- App runs on localhost:3000 — never cloud, never Vercel, never public internet

---

## Agentic action log format
All agent actions must be logged to `./logs/agent-actions.log`:
`[timestamp] [action] [files affected] [outcome]`

